1 L.D. 1343
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 INLAND FISHERIES AND WILDLIFE
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 559, L.D. 1343, “An Act to Protect the
10 Right to Harvest Wildlife”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 29-A in paragraph B in the first line (page 1,
13 line 14 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "sport" and inserting the following:
14 'sustainable use'
15 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 3. 12 MRSA §10050 is enacted to read:
17 §10050. Right to harvest fish and wildlife
18 The Legislature recognizes that the harvesting of fish and wildlife by hunting, fishing
19 or trapping is a valued part of the cultural heritage of this State. The Legislature further
20 recognizes that these activities perform an essential role in the State's economy and in
21 funding the State's management programs for game and nongame species. Such activities
22 also perform an important and sometimes critical role in the biological management of
23 certain fish and wildlife habitats as well as minimizing disease and conflicts with people
24 within this State.
25 In recognition of this cultural heritage and the tradition of stewardship it embodies; in
26 recognition of the important role that the harvesting of fish and wildlife by hunting, fishing
27 or trapping perform in this State's economy and in the preservation and management of the
28 State's fish and wildlife populations; and pursuant to the right to food as declared in the
29 Constitution of Maine, Article I, Section 25, the Legislature declares that the people of this
30 State have the right to harvest fish and wildlife by hunting, fishing or trapping, subject to
31 the applicable laws, rules and regulations authorized pursuant to this Title, which the
32 department shall vigorously enforce.'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
