COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 559, L.D. 1343
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment makes the following changes to the bill. It:
3 1. Removes the section of the bill that provides a definition of the verb "harvest" for
4 the marine resources laws;
5 2. Amends the definition of the verb "harvest" in the bill in the inland fisheries and
6 wildlife laws to clarify that "harvest" means to catch, trap, hunt, fish, take or kill for
7 sustainable use, not for sport; and
8 3. Adds language to clarify that the people of the State have the right to harvest fish as
9 well as wildlife.
